# Login page description
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
** Fields **
- Username field 
- Password field
- Login button 
- Forgot Password link

** Information and specifications of the login page **
The login page provides access to the application. Users are required to enter a valid username and password combination in order to access the system. The username field is a text field that can hold up to 
15 characters and should only contain LETTERS. The password field is a text field that can hold up to 8 characters only. Both the username and password fields should NOT allow spaces. Character limits are set in code 
and the user should not be allowed to enter characters when the limit is reached. Password complexity states that the password should contain at least one uppercase letter and one number and should be at least
4 characters in length. The login button should be disabled by default and only enabled once the username field is populated AND the password field reaches 4 characters in length.

The forgot password link works as follows:
- User clicks the link and is redirected to a forgot-password page.
- The forgot-password page will prompt the user to enter a username.
- if the username is valid, an email with a link will be sent to the users email address.
- when the user opens the email sent and clicks the link, the user should be redirected on a reset-password page and prompted to enter and confirm the new password.
- if the username is not found, the user should remain on the reset-password page and a message is displayed "username <username> not found".

The Login button when clicked should redirect the user to the dashboard page if the username AND password is valid. If the username OR password is invalid, a message should be displayed 
"Incorrect login username or password, please try again".

